					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I'd suggest using the <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">-l</tt> (dash-lowercase-ELL) or <tt style="margin-left: 2px; margin-right: 2px; padding:3px; background-color: #3355aa; color: white;">-L</tt> (dash-uppercase-ELL) flag to generate a listing, and then go through that.  If something is being assembled not quite how you expect (thus generating code that doesn't work how you intended), it'd be in there.<br /><br />Also try running the code under an emulator (e.g. FCEUX) and see what happens, as well as setting a breakpoint at the location the RESET vector points to (assuming you know what address that is in ROM (listing file should help)) and step through things to see what may be misbehaving.</div>

