					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In FCEUX, you can set a reset breakpoint without needing to look at the listing file.<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Open FCEUX for Windows. </li><li>Open your ROM. </li><li>Debug &gt; Debugger </li><li>In the debugger window, click Step Into to stop the program. </li><li>In the game window, NES &gt; Reset. </li><li>In the debugger window, click Step Into again, and the PC will be at the reset vector. </li><li>If expected code isn't here, then either your assembler is configured incorrectly or you've done something wrong in mapper support. </li></ol><br />The &quot;Run Line&quot; and &quot;128 Lines&quot; buttons will be your friend when skipping past spinning on $2002 reads in your init code.</div>

